<HEADLINE>
<P>
COVER STORY: THE PLOTS THICKEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LIBBY SLATE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 All My Children (ABC, noon): Will Gloria discover the truth about Adam's 
kidnaping, and if so, will she change her mind about him? Edmund and Maria's 
marriage may be threatened by Del. Kendall holds the key to Janet's future -- 
will she spill the beans? 
</P>
<P>
 Another World (NBC, 1 p.m.): Can Rachel believe that Carl has turned his life 
around? Jake must convince Paulina to trust him, as both their lives depend on 
it. Iris is caught in a terrifying web of suspense. Tomas' declaration of love 
to Maggie may not be enough when secrets are revealed. 
</P>
<P>
 As the World Turns (CBS, 1 p.m.): Lily faces the prospect of Holden's 
continued interference in her marriage. An unexpected adventure gives rise to 
even more complications for Jessica, Duncan and Shannon. Samantha's reason for 
being in Oakdale is revealed. 
</P>
<P>
 The Bold and the Beautiful (CBS, 12:30 p.m.): Ridge continues to deal with the 
burden of the tragic loss of Taylor. Brooke heads for the altar. Dylan's summer 
internship with Forrester Creations becomes more than he expected. Sheila 
fights Stephanie to hold onto her husband. 
</P>
<P>
 Days of Our Lives (NBC, noon): Lots more romance ahead for Carrie and Austin, 
hampered by Lucas' machinations. The secret to John's past will be revealed.  
</P>
<P>
 General Hospital (ABC, 2 p.m): Ned's amorous juggling act between Lois and 
Katherine becomes more complicated. Mary Mae's rich heritage in Port Charles 
leaves other prominent families fearful of their future. A new arrival turns 
the Spencer household upside down. 
</P>
<P>
 Guiding Light (CBS, 2 p.m.): Vanessa's life changes forever due to a dramatic 
occurrence. Bridget and Dylan realize they belong together, to Julie's 
consternation. The return of Alan Spaulding sends shockwaves through 
Springfield. 
</P>
<P>
 Loving (ABC, 11 p.m.): Angie faces a health crisis, affecting her relationship 
with Frankie and Jeffrey. Trucker's search for his former wife may jeopardize 
his love for Dinah Lee. Steffi and Cooper try to decide what hold Deborah has 
on Clay that forced him to marry her. 
</P>
<P>
 One Life to Live (ABC, 1 p.m.): A jailed Todd is the subject of a campaign for 
early release. Viki finds herself fighting to clear the name of the condemned 
Dorian. Max's continued association with Blair and his gambling troubles may 
spell doom for his marriage to Luna. 
</P>
<P>
 The Young and the Restless (CBS, 11 a.m.): Cricket and Paul search Vietnam for 
a young man whose father may be one of Genoa City's leading residents. Will 
surgery restore the eyesight of Victor's beloved Hope? Victoria's angry actions 
affect her entire family, possibly hurting Cole the most. 
</P>
<P>
 cover lines LIBBY SLATE 
</P>
