<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROLL ALL THE CREDITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I was very interested in the commentary "Go Ahead! Ruin Our Credits" (TV 
Times, May 29).It proved that I was not the only one annoyed by the networks' 
practice of squeezing the closing credits into a corner so they could use the 
extra time to promote upcoming programs. 
</P>
<P>
 The people who worked on a production deserve the recognition. Also, viewers 
should have the opportunity to see who did what on any particular production or 
listen to the theme music instead of irritating promotional chatter. 
</P>
<P>
 Gil Sery, Agoura 
</P>
</TEXT>
