<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOVIES TO TAPE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KEVIN THOMAS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Bring Me the Head of Alfredo Garcia (TNT Thursday at 7:45 p.m.), a rambling 
and lurid tale of an American adrift in Mexico, stars Warren Oates as clearly 
an alter ego for director Sam Peckinpah. 
</P>
<P>
 The Mystery of Picasso (Bravo Saturday at 2:30 p.m.), H.G. Clouzot's beautiful 
1956 documentary, strips away all obstructions to show us white sheets of paper 
being transformed into masterpieces. 
</P>
</TEXT>
