<HEADLINE>
<P>
'LUCY' STILL THE BEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 While watching reruns of "I Love Lucy" on KTTV Channel 11, I am still amazed 
at the great talent of the late Lucille Ball. There is no doubt that "I Love 
Lucy" is the best situation comedy of all time, followed by, in my opinion, the 
wonderfully clever "Beverly Hillbillies" and the clean and good "The Andy 
Griffith Show." 
</P>
<P>
 Most of the highest-rated situation comedies of today are not of the caliber 
of the older programs, as most of the current ones have sexual overtones and 
lack basic good taste. 
</P>
<P>
 Beverly Hall, Glendale 
</P>
</TEXT>
