<HEADLINE>
<P>
PALM LATITUDES: L.A. SPEAK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Judy Raphael 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Comic Collectors' Colloquialisms 
</P>
<P>
 comic condom: n . plastic cover used to practice safe collecting. "I've got 
all my old Silver Surfers in comic condoms ." 
</P>
<P>
 eye tracks: n . facetious term for damage caused by excessive reading. "You've 
been reading that book for so long you've de-minted it with eye tracks. " 
</P>
<P>
 fanboy: n . obsessive collector. 
</P>
<P>
 Kirbyesque: adj. a style inspired by the late Jack Kirby, who helped create 
Captain America, Spider-Man, the Incredible Hulk and the Fantastic Four. 
</P>
<P>
 Marvel zombie: n . fan who buys every issue of Marvel comics, usually has 
superhero power fantasies. Syn. Marvel dweeb. 
</P>
<P>
 mutant head: n . devotee of Mutant comics. 
</P>
<P>
 splash page: n . a full page devoted to one drawing -- usually a battle scene 
or other splashy image. "Boy, those Image books are taken over by splash pages. 
There wasn't any story." 
</P>
<P>
 squid: n . especially annoying fanboy. "The squid sat me down and talked about 
X-Men for two hours."  
</P>
<P>
 stoner: n . head-shop type hooked on R. Crumb, Freak Brothers and other 
druggie comics. Judy Raphael 
</P>
</TEXT>
