<HEADLINE>
<P>
ALBUM REVIEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DON HECKMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * * * Sergio Salvatore, "Tune Up," GRP. Salvatore's first album, recorded when 
he was 12, marked the remarkable arrival of a prodigal new jazz pianist.Now 13, 
his second outing iseven more of a revelation. That Salvatore can swing hard is 
stunningly apparent on pieces such as "Autumn Leaves" and "Au Privave." Even 
more impressive is the subtlety of his dynamic touch on ballads -- especially 
"Almost Home" and "Over the Rainbow" -- and a bristling duet with Chick Corea 
on "Sea Journey." 
</P>
<P>
 Albums are rated on a scale of one star (poor), two stars (fair), three stars 
(good, recommended), four stars (excellent).  
</P>
<P>
 DON HECKMAN 
