<HEADLINE>
<P>
POP MUSIC CHARTS: WARREN G. MUSCLES IN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Of all the artists on the "Above the Rim" soundtrack, rapper Warren G. was the 
biggest scorer, connecting with "Regulate"--recorded with Nate Dogg--which is 
No. 2 on the Time's Southern California pop singles chart. Warren G. parlayed 
that single into a hit debut album, "Regulate...G-Funk Era," which entered the 
Southern California pop chart at No. 1. It also tops the regional and national 
editions of the rap and R&B charts. Being the brother of Dr. Dre and pal of 
Snoop Doggy Dogg undoubtedly helped give Warren G. more clout than most rookie 
rappers. 
</P>
