<HEADLINE>
<P>
JAPANESE YACHTSMAN LANDS AFTER 3 MONTHS AT SEA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Japanese yachtsman landed Friday in the southern port city of Pusan after 
three months drifting at sea, the Yonhap news agency reported. 
</P>
<P>
 Moroi Kiyoji, 56, was on a solo journey across the Pacific from Japan to Los 
Angeles when his mast broke in rough seas near Hawaii on March 8. 
</P>
<P>
 He was rescued by the 17,161-foot freighter Vienna Wood last week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
