STONES FAN CAN'T GET NO SATISFACTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A New Orleans advertising executive lost his bid to play bass guitar with the 
Rolling Stones on one song in exchange for a $50,000 charity donation, but 
local charities still came out winners. 
</P>
<P>
 Herb Montalbano Jr. said Friday that Stones publicist Fran Curtis told him the 
band had nixed his performance, but he decided to give away the $50,000 anyway. 
</P>
<P>
 "Maybe I can help answer some little kid's dream," he said, even though his 
dream of playing with the band remained just that. 
</P>
<P>
 Montalbano said he sent a check for $20,000 to Children's Hospital in New 
Orleans and will divide $30,000 among several other charities, including the 
Humane Society. 
</P>
<P>
 The Stones have included New Orleans on the list of cities they hope to play, 
but no date or location has been announced. 
</P>
