<DATE>
<P>
June 19, 1994, MONDAY 
</P>
</DATE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA061994-0120 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 052702 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
June 19, 1994, Sunday, Ventura West Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Metro; Part B; Page 3; Column 1 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
135 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: THOUSAND OAKS; TEEN-AGERS' PARTY IS BROKEN UP BY VIOLENCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATTHEW MOSK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A party held by a Thousand Oaks teen-ager ended in violence early Saturday 
when 15 gang members broke windows, brandished a gun and beat up a party-goer, 
officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 About 150 teen-agers, including two known gang members, were at a party on 
Westbury Court in Thousand Oaks when 15 people claiming to be from a rival gang 
began breaking the windows, Ventura County sheriff's officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 When one of the party-goers, an 18-year-old youth from Thousand Oaks, went 
outside, an alleged gang member pulled a gun, sheriff's officials said. The 
gang member then struck the 18-year-old in the chin with the gun handle and 
left the scene, officials said. The victim was not hospitalized. 
</P>
<P>
 Sheriff's officials said they have not made any arrests in the case, but it is 
under investigation. MATTHEW MOSK 
</P>
</TEXT>
