<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: THOUSAND OAKS; STING CITES CLERKS WHO SELL ALCOHOL TO MINORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATTHEW MOSK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Ventura County Sheriff's Department sting operation timed to coincide with 
high school graduation parties caught 14 store employees in the act of selling 
alcohol to minors. 
</P>
<P>
 Sheriff's cadets ages 18 and 19 visited about 60 businesses in Moorpark, 
Thousand Oaks and Newbury Park on Friday night and asked to purchase alcoholic 
beverages.  
</P>
<P>
 At 14 of the stores, the sales clerks complied. They were cited and released 
at the scene. 
</P>
<P>
 Sheriff's officials called the sting an effective means of combatting the 
problems associated with young people drinking. 
</P>
<P>
 The program was scheduled to occur during graduation because of the numerous 
end-of-the-year parties being held in the east part of the county, officials 
said. MATTHEW MOSK 
</P>
</TEXT>
