COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; SCHEDULES AVAILABLE FOR NEW BUS SERVICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Route maps and schedules for a new countywide bus service are now available, 
transit leaders have announced. 
</P>
<P>
 The service, called VISTA, is scheduled to begin July 5. 
</P>
<P>
 One line will provide regular service between Simi Valley, Thousand Oaks and 
Moorpark. 
</P>
<P>
 Another will replace Interconnect, a commuter bus service linking Thousand 
Oaks, Camarillo and Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition, new routes will run to large area employers such as Camarillo 
State Hospital and the Navy base at Point Mugu. 
</P>
<P>
 The buses will run Monday through Friday, with fares ranging from $1 to $2 for 
a single ticket and from $31 to $50 for a monthly pass. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (800) 438-1112. SARA CATANIA 
</P>
