<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / THE FIRST ROUND; SPOTLIGHT; REYNA READY, BUT DOES NOT PLAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE CART 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Claudio Reyna did not dress for Saturday's game, although the U.S. team's 
trainer and coaching staff said the midfielder had recovered from a hamstring 
strain. 
</P>
<P>
 Reyna has not trained fully for a week, and U.S. Coach Bora Milutinovic said 
he didn't want to risk further injury. 
</P>
<P>
 "He was ready to go today, but I wanted to give him more rest for the next 
game," Milutinovic said. 
</P>
<P>
 The United States will play Colombia at the Rose Bowl on Wednesday. JULIE CART 
</P>
