<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / THE FIRST ROUND; SPOTLIGHT; APPARENTLY, IT'S HOTTER FOR 
SOME THAN OTHERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HELENE ELLIOTT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Belgian press officer Guido de Windt didn't seem to be amused by midfielder 
Lorenzo Staelens' inability to cope with the high humidity and searing heat 
that have blanketed central Florida since the Belgian team arrived. 
</P>
<P>
 "He is the only player of 22 who can't get used to it," De Windt said. 
</P>
<P>
 If it's exceptionally hot today, Staelens probably won't start. "(Coach Van 
Himst) wants to start with a team that's 100% OK," De Windt said. "If he's not 
100% OK and he has to come out at the half, what good is that?" HELENE ELLIOTT 
