<TEXT>
<P>
 VOYAGE IN THE DARK by Jean Rhys (Norton: $6.95; 188 pp.) . This acclaimed 
novel follows the efflorescence and decline of Anna Morgan, a young woman on 
the brink of adulthood. An emigrant from the West Indies adrift in Great 
Britain, Anna becomes a dancer in minor revues. Briefly taken up by a wealthy 
man, she is unable to accept his failure to return her devotion. In bleak, 
spare prose, Rhys captures the loneliness of a woman who has given everything 
she had and been spurned: Anna's tragedy is not a fantasy of sorrowful passion, 
but a realistic succession of slow hours that must be filled with the 
meaningless activities of daily life. 
</P>
