 THINGS I SHOULD HAVE SAID TO MY FATHER compiled by Joanna Powell (Avon: $10; 
129 pp., paperback original). Mother's Day spawns an unremitting stream of 
mush; Father's Day evokes more complex and often conflicting emotions. In these 
