<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN ESCAPES WITH CASH FROM BANK IN HUNTINGTON BEACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A robber used a note to demand money from a teller at Household Bank and 
escaped with an undetermined amount of cash, police said Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Lt. Luis Ochoa said the robber entered the bank in the 19000 block of Beach 
Boulevard at 11 a.m. and shoved a note to the teller. As the teller opened the 
drawer and reached in for a stack of bills, the robber leaned across the 
counter and also reached into the drawer, Ochoa said. 
</P>
<P>
 The robber, who was wearing a light-colored baseball cap, dark pants and white 
athletic shoes, fled on foot, police said. He never displayed a weapon and no 
injuries were reported. 
</P>
