<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: SOUTHWEST: WEST ADAMS; MINORITY COACHING RECRUITS SOUGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Amateur Athletic Foundation is recruiting aspiring coaches for its 
Minority Coach Leadership Program. 
</P>
<P>
 In the free summer program, young people are trained in coaching soccer and 
swimming. Soccer coaching will be offered in two five-day sessions, Monday 
through Friday and June 27 to July 1. Training for swim coaching comprises 
three weeks of intensive training beginning July 5. 
</P>
<P>
 The philosophy and psychology of coaching, nutrition for athletes, playing 
tactics and strategies, and injury prevention are some of the topics that will 
be covered. 
</P>
<P>
 Ethnic minorities and young women at least 15 years old are encouraged to 
apply. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 730-9632. 
</P>
