<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY; PRESERVATION: CAMERON APPOINTED TO STATE PANEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 David Cameron of Santa Monica has been appointed by Gov. Pete Wilson to the 
State Historical Resources Commission. 
</P>
<P>
 Cameron, a 49-year-old attorney, is a board member of the National Alliance of 
Preservation Commissions and past president of the Santa Monica Historical 
Society. As a member of the Historical Resources Commission, he will help 
develop criteria for the rehabilitation of historic structures and evaluate 
applications for entries to the National Register of Historic Places. 
</P>
<P>
 Commission members do not receive a salary. 
</P>
