<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY; FILM: FRIARS CLUB PLANS TO HONOR CHARLTON HESTON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Friars Club plans to bestow its Lifetime Achievement Award on Charlton 
Heston, it was announced last week. 
</P>
<P>
 The award will be made at a Friars Club dinner July 29 at the Beverly Hilton 
Hotel. The event, to be emceed by Steve Allen, will feature Heston's former 
co-stars and appearances by comics who will reflect on the veteran actor's 
accomplishments. 
</P>
<P>
 Heston has starred in more than 50 motion pictures, including "Ben Hur," for 
which he won a Best Actor Oscar in 1959. 
</P>
<P>
 The Friars Club was founded in New York in 1907 as a nonprofit, charitable 
organization for performers. In 1947, the Los Angeles area branch was formed. 
</P>
