<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASEBALL / DAILY REPORT; AROUND THE MAJOR LEAGUES; 27 INJURED IN CAMDEN YARDS 
ACCIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Twenty-seven people were taken to area hospitals with minor injuries after an 
escalator at Camden Yards in Baltimore jerked to a stop and sent riders falling 
atop each other before Saturday night's game between the Orioles and Minnesota 
Twins. 
</P>
<P>
 The injured were taken to four area hospitals after the accident, which 
occurred about 20 minutes before the game between the Twins and Orioles, said 
Spiro Alafassos, an Oriole spokesman. 
</P>
<P>
 Most of them were transported to the nearby University of Maryland Medical 
Center and the Mercy Medical Center, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's mostly orthopedic problems -- abrasions, lacerations, sprained ankles, 
cuts. At this point it looks like no one will probably need to be admitted," 
she said. 
</P>
<P>
 "It went click-clack and whoosh. It's just like the floor went out from 
underneath us," said Greg Johnson of Brooklyn, Md. 
</P>
<P>
 Alafassos said the escalator would remain shut down until safety inspectors 
arrived to determine the cause of the accident. 
</P>
