<HEADLINE>
<P>
GARDENER'S CHECKLIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 For dedicated gardeners, here are suggestions from the California Assn. of 
Nurserymen on what to do in the garden this week:  
</P>
<P>
 * Water tomatoes, melons and cucumbers deeply every five to seven days for 
large crops. 
</P>
<P>
 * Dust grapes with sulfur for powdery mildew and bunch rot. 
</P>
<P>
 * Fertilize fuchsias and tuberous begonias with fish emulsion. 
</P>
<P>
 * Plant vinca for beautiful flowering color through the heat of summer and 
fall. Available in white, pink, purple, lavender and with contrasting eye. 
</P>
</TEXT>
